Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.93,0:00:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Nshining shooting stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.80,0:00:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.24,0:00:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the Dracula solution!\NThe trick is exposed before sunrise!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.59,0:00:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.42,0:00:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.67,0:01:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man was hired by Mr. Dorakura,\Nowner of Dracula Manor,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.33,0:01:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to investigate his wife's infidelity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.70,0:02:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, someone killed\NMr. Dorakura with a stake to the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.68,0:02:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in his completely-locked study room!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.70,0:02:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To get to the study, one would\Nhave to pass through the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.15,0:02:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where everyone was at the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.27,0:02:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Breaking in from\Noutside was also impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.28,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the killer fly through\Nthe air, like a vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.03,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Dracula Manor Murder Case Part 2."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.37,0:02:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, what a farce that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.80,0:02:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the roof above\Nthe collection room...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those imprints in the snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.85,0:02:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The collection room didn't smell\Nlike oil paint after the incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.44,0:02:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! It doesn't smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that stake not\Nthe source of the smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's first organize what\Nwe know about the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, at around 8:30,\NMr. Dorakura went to the study
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}, Ran, and Conan\Nwent to the collection room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.89,0:03:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to get a film.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.69,0:03:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, the stake used as\Nthe murder weapon was still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.27,0:03:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer\Nstole the stake after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, Ran confirmed that all\Nthe windows in the collection room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.60,0:03:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had been locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.45,0:03:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the only way into the\Nroom was from the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}went to the\Nstudy to deliver the wine and movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:04:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. At around 8:50, I left the\Nwine and film and left the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wine bottle's\Nseal hasn't been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anything seem\Nodd about Mr. Dorakura then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.81,0:04:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You returned to the living\Nroom shortly after 9:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.90,0:04:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then left to make sure\Nthat everything was locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.19,0:04:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I believe I returned\Nten minutes afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The snow had already stopped by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shortly after, his wife\Nretired to her room upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 9:15, I'd say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then she came down when\Nthe body was found around midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, she has no\Nalibi for that period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You left the living room the same\Ntime she did, to go to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I returned to the\Nliving room at about 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means I have no\Nalibi for that period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.89,0:04:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had the opportunity to steal\Nthe stake from the collection room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doi-{\i1}san{\i0}. Right after Hamura-{\i1}san\N{\i0}returned to the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.82,0:05:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you went to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were gone about twenty\Nminutes, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty minutes is enough\Ntime to commit the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I never went\Nto the collection room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Doi-{\i1}san {\i0}only\Nwent to the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.92,0:05:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even bumped into\NHamura-{\i1}san {\i0}on his way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I didn't think of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}. Perhaps you secretly\Nhad the stake when that happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Doi-{\i1}san {\i0}pretended\Nto bump into you and took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit joking around! Why would\NI need to kill Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.82,0:05:51.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'Call of Darkness', by Nakajima Yoshihiko
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These aren't Mr. Dorakura's manuscripts...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.12,0:06:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could they be novels submitted\Nto Doi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s magazine by readers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, it says "Horror Times"\Non the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, \NI have heard an odd rumor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from my university's\NHorror Novel Association,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that novels submitted\Nto the Horror Times
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wound up being\Nplagiarized by Dorakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plagiarized?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you were involved\Nwith this too, Editor-in-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What makes you think--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.11,0:06:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we can compare\NDorakura's manuscripts on this PC
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.91,0:06:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with these submitted novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.62,0:06:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be in your best interest\Nto come clean while you still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.17,0:06:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura... His talent had\Nbeen dried up for years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.13,0:06:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About seven years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I failed in the stock market and\Nfound myself in incredible debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura offered to take over\Nmy debt if I would leak novels to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.56,0:07:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you murdered him to\Ndissolve your relationship, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you have a motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's motives you want,\NTadokoro-{\i1}kun {\i0}has one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was Dorakura's ghostwriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.42,0:07:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ghostwriter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No longer able to endure leaking\Nhim novels submitted to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I introduced him to Tadokoro-{\i1}kun{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.55,0:07:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who I learned of through\Nliterary magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.39,0:07:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't Mr. Dorakura start publishing\Nfantasy works five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}kun{\i0} wrote them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.73,0:07:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true, Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.57,0:07:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't bear a\Ngrudge against him for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:08:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I did, there's\Na reason I couldn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reason you couldn't kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a sister named Kaori,\Nwho's ten years younger than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was born with\Na slightly-faulty heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and as our parents\Ndied when she was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't able to get\Nher decent medical help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, thanks to Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0},\Nshe's now in a hospital in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He offered to pay Kaori's\Nmedical and hospital fees
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.52,0:08:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I became his ghostwriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.15,0:08:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, killing Mr. Dorakura would\Ncut off your sister's treatment...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.07,0:08:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Dorakura sure\Nwas one horrible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.25,0:08:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A true vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the victim was as merciless\Nas a vampire, murder is murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.13,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.22,0:09:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess, unless Hamura-{\i1}san\N{\i0}worked with one of the other two,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the murder would've been impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the only way to get to the\Nonly corridor is from the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.19,0:09:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be impossible to sneak past us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.94,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was possible, the study\Nroom was locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door had a rubber seal,\Nso outside tricks would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, if the window was\Nused to enter and exit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.91,0:09:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only the snow in front\Nof the window had footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon was the wooden\Nstake in the collection room,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the killer was someone\Nin Dracula Manor tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Why did the person\Nkill him with the stake?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That limited the suspects\Nto those inside the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be very bad for the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.31,0:09:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet... why did they\Ndare to use that weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.98,0:09:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:10:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it! There's a\Nslight smell of oil paint left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The windows were locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The small ventilation\Nwindows have spring stoppers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twig piece I found\Non the floor under the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the strange imprints in the\Nsnow on the roof above the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be a connection! What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! So, that's the deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this plastic bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be a secret\Npassageway here somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing of the sort!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.08,0:10:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a good idea who's behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's still a big mystery left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.26,0:11:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how did the killer manage to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.51,0:11:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why did the killer use the\Nprojector to light up the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it just to recreate\Nthe last scene of the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tape? What's it doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.28,0:11:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I know the real reason\Nwhy the killer lit up the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I see the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! There's no secret passage!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-san! Ma'am! Doi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.43,0:11:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me there's\Na real vampire among you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.89,0:11:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A vampire would be able to\Nfly to the study room and back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.02,0:12:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear me. You appear to\Nbe exhausted, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a nice nap and leave\Nthe rest to me, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go again...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's return to our rooms, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.54,0:12:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.67,0:12:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was merely joking before.\NNow, it's time to get down to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Down to business?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.30,0:12:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you suggesting you've\Ndiscovered the truth to this incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.76,0:12:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. All of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us hear your theory then, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the wooden stake\Nused as the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.28,0:12:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought only Hamura-{\i1}san\N{\i0}could have taken the stake,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.95,0:12:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, anyone could\Nhave stolen it from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't a single footstep\Nin the snow outside, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no footprints because\Nthe killer walked through the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walked through the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this another of your jokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.01,0:13:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you aware that the window\Nby the entrance hall is as high up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the roof above\Nthe collection room window?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used that fact to\Nmake a bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.35,0:13:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,using a ladder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ladder?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.31,0:13:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walking across it, the killer could\Nget to the collection room window
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without leaving any footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, there are ladder\Nmarks on the snow on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.99,0:13:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the windows were locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They could easily be\Nopened with a simple little trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.92,0:13:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sticking the twig piece Conan found
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.59,0:13:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,between the ventilation\Nwindow's stopper and the glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, the stopper\Nwill look like it's set,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.01,0:13:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the window can\Nstill be opened freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer stole the stake from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.39,0:14:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, simply closing the\Nwindow would make the stopper lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! The stake was\Ntwo meters from that window!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.90,0:14:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used a tree pruner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.99,0:14:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You used one this afternoon,\NTadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are attachments\Nfor those for picking fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer attached one and stuck\Nit through the ventilation window
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to steal the stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.30,0:14:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this method, anyone\Ncould have obtained the stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.93,0:14:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, how did the\Nperson go to the study and back?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simple, by crossing the corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.19,0:14:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NThat's absolute nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.44,0:14:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it much more logical than\Nhaving the killer fly through the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in the living room, too.\NYou know no one used the corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.83,0:15:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but one person did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.62,0:15:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was you, Tadokoro Toshiya-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.01,0:15:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stake was still in the collection\Nroom when I went to the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.35,0:15:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.64,0:15:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, what you two saw was\Nan elaborately-made fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.15,0:15:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}went to get\Nthe film, he invited you and Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.16,0:15:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and showed you the stake, so you\Nwould confirm it had been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.83,0:15:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, after killing Mr. Dorakura\Nwith the real stake,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.87,0:15:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which he had hidden\Nin the study in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he pretended to check all\Nthe locks and stole the fake stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}. Do you have\Nproof the stake was a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This turned up after I instructed\NConan to look through the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's very well-made.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the fake blood\Nadded using oil paint?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife does oil painting, so it\Nwould've been easy to get the paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.54,0:16:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}. Even if he did use\Nthe corridor to reach the study,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how did he get inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was locked from the inside,\Nso he couldn't have gone out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if he left through the window,\Nhow did he return to the corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.39,0:16:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no other footprints,\Nexcept those in front of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.94,0:16:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The open window and the trampled\Nsnow were simply a red herring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.69,0:16:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}entered\Nand exited through the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how could I have\Nlocked it from the outside?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Locking the door is no problem at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.12,0:17:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you use that projector, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Projector?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?\NHow could a projector do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0},\NI've figured it all out, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Including why you lit up the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it to recreate\Nthe last scene of the movie?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The body was lit up to\Ncamouflage the real reason
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for moving the projector!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.61,0:17:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For this trick to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was absolutely vital to move\Nthe projector in front of the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the trick would be obvious\Nif only the projector were moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, by lighting up the body as\Na bit of an informed performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our attention was diverted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.30,0:17:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll now reenact this trick I speak of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.14,0:18:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Lend me a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, pull about five\Nmeters of film from the reel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, stick a piece of\Ntape on the end of the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, throw the film over\Nthe blackout curtain rail by the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and attach it to the lock on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.25,0:18:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All done, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now everything is set.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Start the projector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how Tadokoro-{\i1}san\N{\i0}locked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, unfortunately for him,\Nas the film was being pulled in,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the piece of tape caught on\Nthe curtain rail and remained there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.92,0:19:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the piece of tape are small,\Nsquare marks... from perforations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The square holes in\Nthe film, in other words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}, can you\Ngive any other explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as to why that perforation-marked\Ntape was stuck on the curtain rail?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.77,0:19:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's about\Ntime you tell us the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already confessed you were\Nthe killer when the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.58,0:19:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, you said\Nyou could hear the projector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you find that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.83,0:19:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door had airtight,\Nsound-proof rubber sealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:19:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you hear\Nwhat was happening inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that the\Nprojector was on inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.14,0:20:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, shall we see if the projector is\Naudible behind the closed door?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.10,0:20:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would you kill Dorakura-{\i1}san{\i0}?!\NWhat about your sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.78,0:20:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister... Kaori... has\Nbeen dead for a year now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura never gave\NKaori real medical treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He paid off her doctor so she\Nwould get neither better nor worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.64,0:20:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just to keep Kaori hospitalized longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.85,0:21:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, then her condition suddenly\Ntook a turn for the worse, and she...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only found out about\Nthis one month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.82,0:21:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura kept my sister's\Ndeath secret the entire time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed his lie about sending her\Nto a better hospital in America...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, one month ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.17,0:21:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori's nurse couldn't bear it\Nanymore and secretly came to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.93,0:21:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said Kaori deliriously cried\Nmy name over and over as she died...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.10,0:21:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had, had real treatment...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.56,0:21:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had had real treatment,\Nthat never would've happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.53,0:21:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura murdered Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.57,0:21:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why... That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.87,0:22:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say a vampire's bite can turn\Na normal person into a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unknowingly, Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}might\Nhave become a vampire himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A vampire known as a murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franken Manor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.27,0:23:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It belongs to Furano Kenzo,\Nan engineering professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.61,0:23:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he conducts strange\Nexperiments every night and--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.98,0:23:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time it's Frankenstein...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:23:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just need\Na wolfman and we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.49,0:24:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Shiraki!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.76,0:24:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's not right!\NWhat could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.14,0:24:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.76,0:24:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was in the dressing room,\Nthe flower on his chest was--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.77,0:24:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Okano Rika-{\i1}san {\i0}is the killer,\Nwho will she go after next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.35,0:24:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!\NWho is she trying to kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.49,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!\NI'm not gonna make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan:\N"The Flower Scent Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.30,0:24:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.77,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode fits me perfectly. Smells like flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.12,0:24:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes pretty flowers have thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.99,0:24:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
